***** {{tact|end}}
*** {{topt|Actually, my current cape is fine.}}
**** '''Kolodion:''' I see... If you ever change your mind, you know where to find me.
**** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Kolodion again===
* {{tcond|If the player doesn't have an enchanted symbol:}}
** '''Kolodion:''' Here, take this enchanted symbol of the gods. It will guide you to the creatures.
** {{tbox|pic=Enchanted symbol detail.png|Kolodion hands you an enchanted symbol.}}
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|If the player doesn't have an enchanted symbol and their inventory is full:}}
** '''Kolodion:''' You'll need to free up an inventory space before we continue.
** {{tact|continues}}
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|Where can I find these beings?}}
*** '''Player:''' Where can I find these beings?
*** '''Kolodion:''' They can all be found in the Wilderness. The enchanted symbol can track their unique magical energies, leading you to their exact locations.
*** '''Kolodion:''' Be warned though, the symbol will take a blood sacrifice every time it's used.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Any advice on fighting the beings?}}
*** '''Player:''' Any advice on fighting the beings?
*** '''Kolodion:''' They can't be harmed by normal magic, melee or ranged attacks, you will need to use the god combat spell corresponding to the creature you are fighting.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Tell me more about these beings.}}
*** '''Player:''' Tell me more about these beings.
*** '''Kolodion:''' One is a justiciar. According to legend, the justiciars were the elite of Saradomin's forces. Some worked alone, operating as assassins behind enemy lines. Others led entire armies in Saradomin's name.
*** '''Kolodion:''' I couldn't tell you why this one wanders the Wilderness, but I suspect he has good reason.
*** '''Kolodion:''' The second is a Demon of Zamorak. From what I can tell, he is completely mad. He roams the Wilderness, killing all who he comes across without mercy. Even his own kind do not escape his fury.
*** '''Kolodion:''' He's known to battle the justiciar quite regularly, perhaps they are old enemies.
*** '''Kolodion:''' The final being is a Guthixian Ent. Like most followers of Guthix, he will avoid combat if possible. Make no mistake though, he is deadly when threatened.
*** '''Kolodion:''' He seems to take great interest in the other two creatures. Maybe he is trying to keep a balance between them.
*** '''Kolodion:''' All three of them give off a unique magical energy, one unlike any I have ever felt before. The fact that the three of them are so different, yet possess powers so similar, is very odd indeed.
*** '''Kolodion:''' I'd be very interested in learning more about the source of their power.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Thanks, bye.}}
*** '''Player:''' Thanks, bye.
*** '''Kolodion:''' Farewell, [player name].
*** {{tact|end}}

